4. Methodology

The system analyzes several telemetry parameters including:

Signal Strength

Packet Loss

Network Latency

Frequency Variation

Encryption Status

These parameters are used as input features for machine learning models. The Random Forest algorithm is trained to classify attack types based on these features. Isolation Forest detects anomalies by identifying unusual data patterns.

Additionally, a deep learning neural network model is trained to improve detection accuracy by identifying complex relationships between telemetry parameters.

The system processes user inputs through a web interface and generates predictions about potential threats in the satellite communication network.



